nied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes of Thame was born about 1194, in Thame, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Richard Foliot."},"et":{"about 1194–":"umbes 1194–Surnud","1185–1225":"1185–1225","1215–1268":"1215–1268","1194–Female":"1194–Surnud","about 1194":"umbes 1194","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1268":"1268","Abt 1215":"umbes 1215","1185":"1185","1194":"1194","Thame,Oxfordshire,England.":"Thame, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1194–":"noin 1194–Kuollut","1185–1225":"1185–1225","1215–1268":"1215–1268","1194–Female":"1194–Kuollut","about 1194":"noin 1194","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1268":"1268","Abt 1215":"noin 1215","1185":"1185","1194":"1194","Thame,Oxfordshire,England.":"Thame, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1194–":"environ 1194–Décédée","1185–1225":"1185–1225","1215–1268":"1215–1268","1194–Female":"1194–Décédée","about 1194":"environ 1194","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1268":"1268","Abt 1215":"environ 1215","1185":"1185","1194":"1194","Thame,Oxfordshire,England.":"Thame, Oxfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Agnes of Thame est née environ 1194, à Thame, Oxfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fi